the ghost and mrs. muir ( 1947 ) is a fantasy romantic comedy-drama film starring gene tierney and rex harrison . the director was joseph l. mankiewicz . it is based on a 1945 novel written by josephine leslie under the pseudonym of r. a. dick . in 1945 , 20th century fox bought the film rights to the novel , which had been published only in the united kingdom at that time . it was shot entirely in california .